\c 31
\s1 Mazmur yang ditulis oleh Daud untuk Pemimpin Pujian
\q1
\v 1 Untuk pemimpin musik; sebuah mazmur dari Daud.
\q2 Pada-Mu, TUHAN, aku berlindung!
\q1 Jangan biarkan aku dipermalukan!
\q1 Pulihkanlah nama baikku dengan menyelamatkanku!
\q1
\v 2 Dengarkan dan perhatikan aku!
\q1 Cepatlah selamatkan aku!
\q1 Jadilah penjaga dan pelindungku,
\q1 bentengku tempat aku bisa selamat!
\q1
\v 3 Karena Engkaulah gunung batuku dan bentengku;
\q2 demi reputasi-Mu sendiri Engkau memimpinku dan membimbingku.
\q1
\v 4 Kaulah yang akan membebaskanku dari jaring tersembunyi yang mereka tempatkan untukku.
\q2 karena Engkaulah tempat perlindunganku.
\q1
\v 5 Ke dalam tangan-Mu aku percayakan hidupku;
\q1 Kau akan menyelamatkanku, Ya TUHAN, Allah yang setia.
\v 6 Aku benci kepada para penyembah patung yang tidak berguna,
\q2 tapi kepada-Mu aku percaya.
\q1
\v 7 Aku senang dan bergembira dalam kesetiaan-Mu,
\q1 karena Kau menyadari kesulitanku
\q2 dan kau menyadari saat-saat aku tertekan.
\q1
\v 8 Kau tidak mengirimku ke tangan kuasa musuhku;
\q2 Kau membuat aku bertahan di tempat yang luas dan terbuka.
\v 9 Kasihanilah kau, karena aku sedang tertekan!
\q1 Mataku tidak bisa melihat karena berduka.
\q2 Aku telah kehilangan kekuatanku.
\q1
\v 10 Dalam kesakitan hidupku hampir mendekati akhirnya;
\q2 tahun-tahunku mendekat saat aku mengerang.
\q1 dan Aku menjad lemah karena dosaku,
\q2 dan tulang-tulangku menjadi rapuh.
\q1
\v 11 All of my enemies make fun of me,
\q2 and even my neighbors despise me.
\q1 Even my friends are afraid of me \add because they think I am being punished byGod\add*,
\q2 and when they see me on the streets, they run away.
\q1
\v 12 People have forgotten me like they forget people who are dead.
\q2 \add They think I am as useless\add* as a broken pot.
\q1
\v 13 I have heard people slandering me,
\q2 and they have caused me to become terrified.
\q1 My enemies are making plans
\q2 in order to kill me.
\b
\q1
\v 14 But Yahweh, I trust in you.
\q2 You are my God.
\q1
\v 15 My whole life [MTY] is in your hands;
\q2 save me from my enemies,
\q2 from those who pursue me.
\q1
\v 16 Act kindly toward me
\q2 and rescue me because you always faithfully love me.
\q1
\v 17 Yahweh, I call out to you,
\q2 so do not allow me to be disgraced.
\q1 I desire that wicked people will be disgraced;
\q2 I desire/hope that they will \add soon die and\add* go down to the place where the dead people are.
\q1
\v 18 I desire that you will cause people [MTY] who tell lies to be unable to speak.
\q2 Do that for people who are proud and those who arrogantly accuse righteous people.
\b
\q1
\v 19 You have stored up many great and good things to do for those who have an awesome respect for you.
\q2 You do those good things for those who go to you to be protected;
\q2 everyone sees you doing that.
\q1
\v 20 You hide people in your presence where it is safe,
\q2 and protect them from people who plot \add to kill them\add*.
\q1 You hide them in safe places from their enemies [MTY] who accuse/insult them.
\b
\q1
\v 21 Praise Yahweh!
\q2 When my enemies surrounded the city \add in which I was living\add*,
\q2 he showed me wonderfully that he faithfully loves me.
\q1
\v 22 I was afraid, and I cried out, “I have been separated from Yahweh!”
\q2 but you heard me and answered my cry for help.
\b
\q1
\v 23 You people who belong to Yahweh, love him!
\q2 Those who are loyal to him, he protects,
\q2 but those who are very proud, he punishes them severely like they deserve to be punished.
\q1
\v 24 You who confidently expect Yahweh \add to do great things foryou\add*,
\q2 be strong, be courageous!